001package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.parameters;
002
003import io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.quest.SuperQuest;
004import java.util.function.Consumer;
005
006/**
007 * Defines a contract for cleaning up test data after execution.
008 *
009 * <p>Implementations of this interface specify cleanup logic for removing
010 * test-generated data, ensuring that test environments remain in a consistent state.
011 *
012 * <p>The cleanup operation is executed via a {@link Consumer} that accepts a {@link SuperQuest} instance.
013 * Each implementation also provides an enumeration reference for structured identification.
014 *
015 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate ğŸ’ğŸ‘¨ğŸ’»
016 */
017public interface DataRipper<T extends Enum<T>> {
018
019   /**
020    * Provides the cleanup operation for test-generated data.
021    *
022    * <p>Implementations return a {@link Consumer} that defines the cleanup logic,
023    * allowing for structured and reusable test data removal.
024    *
025    * @return A {@link Consumer} responsible for executing the cleanup process.
026    */
027   Consumer<SuperQuest> eliminate();
028
029   /**
030    * Returns the enumeration instance associated with the cleanup operation.
031    *
032    * <p>This ensures that cleanup actions can be identified and referenced
033    * in a structured manner within the framework.
034    *
035    * @return An {@link Enum} instance representing the cleanup operation.
036    */
037   T enumImpl();
038
039}
